---
const title = "Caaligo | Videos";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
  <title>{title}</title>
</head>

<body>

  <aside class="sidebar">

    <div class="brand">
      <img src="/channellogo.jpg" alt="Caaligo Logo" class="channel-logo" />
      <h1>CAALIGO</h1>
      <p>
        Minecraft creator making videos,
        mods, and more.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="search">
      <input type="text" placeholder="Search..." />
    </div>

    <nav>
      <h3>Navigation</h3>
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <a href="/content" class="active">Videos</a>
      <a href="/moe">Obsidian Edition</a>
      <a href="/blog">Blog</a>
      <a href="/community">Community</a>
      <a href="/about">About</a>
    </nav>

    <nav>
      <h3>Socials</h3>
      <a href="#">YouTube</a>
      <a href="#">Discord</a>
    </nav>

  </aside>

  <main class="main">

    <article class="paper">

      <div class="hero">
        <p class="label">CONTENT ARCHIVE</p>

        <h2>Videos</h2>

        <p>
          Minecraft documentaries, ARG investigations, and project devlogs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <section>
        <h3>Latest Uploads</h3>

        <div class="video-grid">

          <div class="video-card">
            <iframe
              src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/9WrYbEGEaNI"
              title="Playing a Minecraft Version That Never Existed"
              frameborder="0"
              allowfullscreen>
            </iframe>

            <h4>Playing a Minecraft Version That Never Existed</h4>

            <p>
              Exploring the world and mechanics of Minecraft Obsidian Edition.
            </p>

            <a href="https://youtube.com/watch?v=9WrYbEGEaNI" target="_blank">
              Watch on YouTube
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="video-card">
            <iframe
              src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/4bFueBEvSBo"
              title="Every Mod on the Minecraft Mod Iceberg Explained (Part 2)"
              frameborder="0"
              allowfullscreen>
            </iframe>

            <h4>Every Mod on the Minecraft Mod Iceberg Explained (Part 2)</h4>

            <p>
              Exploring the history, development, and stories behind legendary Minecraft mods.
            </p>

            <a href="https://youtube.com/watch?v=4bFueBEvSBo" target="_blank">
              Watch on YouTube
            </a>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="category-section">
        <h3>Unfiction & ARG Analysis</h3>
        <p class="section-desc">Deep dives into strange discoveries, horror projects, and web mysteries.</p>

        <div class="video-grid">

          <div class="video-card">
            <iframe
              src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/_kFwQPv4X5A"
              title="Caedes ARG Analysis"
              frameborder="0"
              allowfullscreen>
            </iframe>

            <h4>Caedes ARG Analysis</h4>

            <p>
              Investigating the hidden layers of the Minecraft Caedes ARG.
            </p>

            <a href="https://youtube.com/watch?v=_kFwQPv4X5A" target="_blank">
              Watch on YouTube
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="category-section">
        <h3>Most Recent</h3>
        <p class="section-desc">My most recent upload to my YouTube channel.</p>

        <div class="video-grid">

          <div class="video-card">
            <iframe
              src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/4bFueBEvSBo"
              title="Every Mod on the Minecraft Mod Iceberg Explained (Layer 2)"
              frameborder="0"
              allowfullscreen>
            </iframe>

            <h4>Every Mod on the Minecraft Mod Iceberg Explained (Layer 2)</h4>

            <p>
              In this video, I return to the Minecraft Mod Iceberg, completing layer two. I go through classic mods, like Orespawn, Chocolate Quest, the Aether I and II, and more. Join us as we dive into some of the most influential mods in Minecraft's history.
            </p>

            <a href="#" target="_blank">
              Watch on YouTube
            </a>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

    </article>

  </main>

</body>
</html>

<style>
:root {
  --accent: #58c7ff;
  --purple: #8c7cff;
  --paper: #ffffff;
}

body {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
  background-image: url("/space.jpg");
  background-size: cover;
  background-position: center;
  background-attachment: fixed;
}

/* Sidebar */
.sidebar {
  position: fixed;
  width: 280px;
  height: 100vh;
  background: rgba(17,20,38,0.95);
  padding: 35px;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  color: white;
  overflow-y: auto;
}

/* Sidebar Channel Logo */
.channel-logo {
  width: 110px;
  height: 110px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  object-fit: cover;
  margin-bottom: 15px;
  border: 2px solid var(--accent);
  box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(88, 199, 255, 0.2);
}

.brand h1 {
  margin: 0;
  font-size: 42px;
  letter-spacing: 5px;
}

.brand p {
  color: #b8bfd8;
  line-height: 1.5;
}

.search input {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 10px;
  margin: 25px 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  background: #20243b;
  border: 1px solid #333;
  color: white;
}

nav {
  margin-bottom: 35px;
}

nav h3 {
  color: var(--accent);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  font-size: 13px;
  letter-spacing: 2px;
}

nav a {
  display: block;
  color: #cfd5ed;
  text-decoration: none;
  padding: 8px 0;
}

nav a:hover, nav a.active {
  color: white;
}

nav a.active {
  font-weight: bold;
  border-left: 2px solid var(--accent);
  padding-left: 10px;
  margin-left: -12px;
}

/* Main */
.main {
  margin-left: 280px;
  padding: 50px;
  min-height: 100vh;
}

.paper {
  max-width: 850px;
  margin: auto;
  background: var(--paper);
  padding: 55px;
  box-shadow: 0 20px 60px black;
}

.hero {
  text-align: center;
}

.label {
  color: #777;
  letter-spacing: 3px;
}

.hero h2 {
  font-size: 42px;
  margin-top: 10px;
}

.hero p {
  color: #555;
  font-size: 18px;
}

hr {
  border: none;
  border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
  margin: 40px 0;
}

h3 {
  font-size: 24px;
}

/* Category Sections */
.category-section {
  margin-top: 50px;
}

.section-desc {
  color: #666;
  margin-top: -15px;
  margin-bottom: 25px;
  font-size: 15px;
}

/* Grid and iFrame Sizing */
.video-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr));
  gap: 25px;
}

.video-card {
  background: #f2f4f8;
  padding: 20px;
  border-left: 5px solid var(--accent);
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}

.video-card iframe {
  width: 100%;
  height: 200px;
  border: none;
  background: #000;
}

.video-card h4 {
  margin: 15px 0 10px 0;
}

.video-card p {
  margin-top: 0;
  flex-grow: 1;
}

.video-card a {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-top: 10px;
  background: #111426;
  color: white;
  padding: 10px 18px;
  text-decoration: none;
  align-self: flex-start;
}

@media(max-width:900px) {
  .sidebar {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }
  .main {
    margin-left: 0;
    padding: 20px;
  }
  .paper {
    padding: 30px;
  }
}
</style>